<br>
yes, and that is what makes this such a spectacular work of art.<br>
<br>
As for the religious imagary, it goes far beyond christian mythos.  I don't feel like going back and pulling for quotes, but go back over the last few pages and read my posts... the god and goddess allusions blew me away!<br>
Of course, some people whine and cry ... &quot;it was stupid, I hated it!  Some stupid movie about stupid gods and monsters with stupid people saying stupid things I didn't understand.&quot;<br>
<br>
The child ... she was a child.  She had the curiosity and innosence of a child, and she was not afraid of her creative energies, or thinking they were a waste of time.  She was not borneof a purpose, she was borne of love, but this is significant for two reasons.  First, it shows her as a true child, something that is, not for a purpose, but to be.  BUT ... it also shows the programs learning to understand the human connections that are a part of these emotions.  <br>
The oracle isn't patronizing her in the end, she is praising her for using her creative energies.  She didn't create a sunrise because she was created to, she didit becasue she wanted to.  The oracle is complimenting her for that.<br>
<br>
As for Neo, he is dead, and he isn't.<br>
When he combined with Smith, he did destroy Neo as he and smith deleted each other, BUT ... as the oracle pointed out, The One will return when it is time.  In that way, The One isn't dead, though Neo CERTIANLY is.  Neo learned from Trinity (like most ... and I do mean MOST... men do learn from women... but I digress).  Trinity sacraficed herself to get Neo inside, and then explained to him that he made her life complete by letting her make a sacrafice of this level to him.  In turn, he made THAT SAME sacrafice to the machines AND to the humans.  Yes, Neo is dead.  I liked the portrayal of him as a christ figure in the end adn I also like that you don't actually know what happened to his body.  Was it burried by the machines?  I like to think so...<br>
<br>
but we will never actually know.<br>
<br>
I like that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=usildordhujata>Usildor Dhujata</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crypt Pimp</span><br>  Posts: 1168<br> <font color=#330000>(11/10/03 4:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1118.topic&index=88>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/poeticsarcasm/images/marblemn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: Matrix Revolutions...</span><hr size=1> Probably turned him into a liquid margarita and fed him to the matrix denizens as described in the first movie.  Neo tar tar anyone? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
