<br>
I like my movies to be my &quot;escape&quot; or &quot;vacation&quot; from life...<br>
<br>
..i &quot;think&quot; enough at work, or even at home for that matter, when I go to the movies I don't always want to think, I want to soak it in and enjoy, relax, even get sucked in to the fantasy, etc etc.<br>
<br>
I think the matrix did a good job of giving both sides to the audience, it had a part that you could dwell on, but it could also be taken at face value without too much thought.<br>
<br>
To me that is what made it good, there are too many movies that are so thoughtless they are boring, and others that are SO thought-provoking that you cant even relax enough to &quot;get into&quot; the movie much less stay awake. A good balance is ummm good.<br>
<br>
I don't think it makes someone stupid to NOT want to think about a movie...Jumping down someone's throat about not thinking enough about a movie is like yelling at someone for going to Disney World and not at all getting the fact that &quot;Mr Toad's Wild Ride&quot; is really a statement on the plight of the hetero male in today's politically correct pro-gay society. Sometime's it's just fun to be entertained. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/88/88432/pages/399981/gnipcola.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chuddmidgetlover>chudd midgetlover</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#330000>(11/11/03 9:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1118.topic&index=91>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: Matrix Revolutions...</span><hr size=1> revolutions was the best of the 3 only because you got to see keanu reeves die. the ending fight seen couldn't have been gayer unless neo and agent smith did a standing 69. they copied the gun fight scene from the first movie, only difference was that they walked on the ceiling in revolutions. the black guy on the council should have spoke jive. the acting in the movie was incredibly overdramatic and bad. keanu reeves is a bad actor and a horrible musician, he should stop acting and get rid of his band.  <p>65 rogue Optimis<br>
